<section id="command-bitloadsize">
    <title>BITLOADSIZE</title>
<indexterm><primary>BITLOADSIZE</primary></indexterm>

<variablelist>

<varlistentry><term>Synopsis</term>
<listitem>
<synopsis><command>BITLOADSIZE</command> <parameter>filename</parameter></synopsis>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry><term>Description</term>
<listitem>
<para>
Output the width and height of the bitmap that is specified by the <parameter>filename</parameter> input.
The <parameter>filename</parameter> input must be a word that is the name of valid bitmap file.
</para>
<para>
The output is a two-member list of the form [width height].
</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry><term>Example</term>
<listitem>
<programlisting><userinput>SHOW BITLOADSIZE "c:\\windows\\forest.bmp</userinput>
[256 256]
</programlisting>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

</variablelist>

</section>
